cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.SY. 

The paper discusses a new evaluation platform for reinforcement learning agents, which suggests it could belong to several sub-categories. The focus on representation learning and behavioural learning suggests it could be in cs.LG (Machine Learning), while the use of Atari games and the focus on visual input suggests it could also be in cs.CV (Computer Vision). The evaluation of different architectures and components suggests it could be in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the use of eligibility traces suggests it could be in cs.SY (Systems and Control).
